XML - eXtensible Markup Language

XML looks very similar to HTML. 
the structure of a xml is like a tree. 
	the intend of XML points to catch the nested structure
	you should think to the attribute as a child

In Microsoft the x in the end means that it is using the XML. They use XML to define bold, italic...
pptx for example



In XML you have *elements* or *Nodes*

Simple Element		tag - text - tag
Complex Element		tag - tag- text - tag -tag 


start Tag		<person>
End Tag			</name>
Text Content		text inside the tag
Attribute		
Self Closing tag	<email/>


Terminology:

Tags 		indicates the beginning and the ending of elements
Attributes	Keyword/value pairs on the opening tag of XML
Serialize	
